      <div id="slide" class="slide1">      
        <div class="inside-slide">
          <div class="slide-title">
            <p>What is a solar flare</p>
          </div>
          <div class="slide-content content1">
            <ul>
              <li>A solar flare is a large explosion in the Sun's atmosphere that can release an amazing amount of energy.</li>
              <li>The approximate energy release is 6 x 10<sup>25</sup> joules of energy.</li>
              <li>That is equivalent to millions of 100-megaton hydrogen bombs exploding at the same time or ten million times greater than
              the energy released by a volcanic erupition.</li> 
              <li>These energy bursts can be about 1/6 of the total output of the sun's energy each second.</li>
              <li>They often appear around sun spots</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="span-8">
              <%= link_to image_tag("flare2-thumb.jpg", :id => "below-gallery", :class=>"media-in-slide"),
              '/images/flare2.jpg', :rel => "prettyPhoto[slide1-image]", :title => "Solar flares with the sun blocked out for better visualization."%>
              <%= image_tag("flare2.jpg", :class => "earthquake_screen") %>
            </div>
            <div class="span-10">
              <p>
              Click the image to enlarge. The image has the sun's solar disk blocked out so the solar flare can be visualized better.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="slide-number-left">
            <p>1</p>
          </div>
          <div class="slide-number-right">
            <p>1</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
        <div id="slide" class="slide2">      
          <div class="inside-slide">
            <div class="slide-title">
              <p>Solar Flare Footage</p>
            </div>
            <div class="slide-content content2">
              <br/>
              <div class="span-11">
                <div class="media-in-slide" style="width: 400px">
                  <script type="text/javascript" src="http://cdn-akm.vmixcore.com/vmixcore/js?auto_play=0&cc_default_off=1&player_name=uvp&width=400&height=400&player_id=1aa0b90d7d31305a75d7fa03bc403f5a&t=c2c5ba1bd1405638772509926ce0062d"></script>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="span-6">
                <p>
                Footage taken from Nasa's Solar Dynamics Observatory. The visual is being shown in ultra violet light.
                It is the largest solar flare since December 5, 2006.
                </p>
              </div>
            <%= link_to image_tag("flare1-thumb.jpg", :id => "below-gallery", :class=>"media-in-slide"),
              '/images/flare1.jpg', :rel => "prettyPhoto[slide2-image]", :title => "Solar flare image captured in ultraviolet light. The white vertical lines are from the overwhelming flash of light from the solar flare."%>
